reviews.review_text: Theres a couple of women who regularly work the morning shift at the drive thru windows. One takes payment, the other gives you your order. They are awesome. Friendly, smiling, upbeat and a pleasure to see each time we would grab a coffee or breakfast. I give them 5 stars But in the evenings the kids working are robotic, impersonal, and do not exhibit the friendly helpful manners of customer service. The ice cream machines always broken. I cant get less ice in my drink, even when i request it. The cold drinks have more ice than soda, yet mcdonalds limits the drink orders because they dont have enough ice. It was hot out, we were all thirsty, and only 4 out of five of us were allowed to buy a drink. I couldnt order any cold drink even if I didnt want ice in mine. If mcdonalds used less ice in the fountain drinks, customers could get enough liquid to wash down their meal, and they could hydrate more customers. But they dont have what their signs have advertising 60% of the time. Gets frustrating
Its not bad but Sometimes the Food is cold they have good Service and the Atmosphere is Really nice. And the food is always fresh make you wait a little bit but thats a good thing.
To the morning manager working on Saturday August 5 2023.  Thank you. Your excellent work does not go unseen .
I recommend this McDonald s because the worker Reta was doing an amazing wonderful job, I got my food really fast hot and ready and she was so sweet !

Today between 2- 3am I visited here.They served me a fresh and hot food. It s was lineup but then also they were taking all the orders turn by turn. The girl took my payment was so polite with me. Best customer service and quality of food from all Mac Donald s I say.

The staff asked a sketchy man who had taken over the washroom to leave, a large customer stuck up for him. Dear Large customer, when children cant use the washroom, let the staff do their job. The guy was leaving, he didnt need you to cause a scene but since you did he manipulated you out of a donation. He conned you, big time!! Job well done to Elena and her supervisor

Needed lunch while waiting for my tire to be repaired. Walked over to the McDonalds next door. Found signage hard to read until I realized it rotates between menus. Ordered my lunch and sat down to wait for number to be called. A little confusion because a group arrived to order and there were many voices competing and I missed my order being called. Realizing what had happened I walked up and asked if the tray sitting on the counter was mine.  The lady very nicely checked and said it was. Well worth it the wrap was delicious and I had lots of time.
